Guyana's Jagan Has 
Ideals but Few Deals

PARAGRAPH.#text:
President Cheddi Jagan
 of Guyana is
the last of the anticolonial liberation leaders still on the job -- and at
age 78, he's as fiery as ever about ridding the world of injustice. But
many wish Mr. Jagan would get back to basics by cutting red tape, paving
the country's horrendous roads and getting the electricity to work for more
than a few hours a day.
